"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-sports-2024-9-2-paris-mayors-plan-to-keep-olympic-rings-on-eiffel-tower-sparks-criticism\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Critics say keeping the rings on the Paris landmark will be akin to making it 'an advertising outpost'.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 37, \"end\": 42, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1737593392155295e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Critics\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 7}, {\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 20, \"to\": 29}, {\"ngram\": \"an advertising outpost\", \"from\": 79, \"to\": 101}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Save Share Plans to keep the Olympic rings on the Eiffel Tower have come under criticism by descendants of the Paris landmark's designer and have provoked a backlash from some locals.\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 218, \"end\": 223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1737593392155295e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Save Share\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 115}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic rings\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 147}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 151, \"to\": 167}, {\"ngram\": \"criticism\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 193}, {\"ngram\": \"descendants\", \"from\": 197, \"to\": 208}, {\"ngram\": \"a backlash\", \"from\": 260, \"to\": 270}, {\"ngram\": \"some locals\", \"from\": 276, \"to\": 287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The giant rings were a popular addition to the monument for visitors and tourists in Paris during the July 28 to August 11 Olympic Games in the French capital.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 377, \"end\": 382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1737593392155295e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 436, \"end\": 442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8512956349131848, \"rank\": 0.14286485839078722, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The giant rings\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 307}, {\"ngram\": \"a popular addition\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 331}, {\"ngram\": \"the monument\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 347}, {\"ngram\": \"visitors\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 360}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mayor Anne Hidalgo announced on Saturday that she intended to take down the originals, which are too heavy to remain on the monument, and replace them with new rings.\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 459, \"end\": 471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 493}, {\"ngram\": \"the originals\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 538}, {\"ngram\": \"the monument\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 585}, {\"ngram\": \"new rings\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 618}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It does not seem appropriate to us that the Eiffel Tower, which has become the symbol of Paris and the whole of France since its construction 135 years ago, has the symbol of an outside organisation added to it in a permanent way, whatever its prestige,\\\" a statement from the Association of Gustave Eiffel's Descendants said.\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 711, \"end\": 716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1737593392155295e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 734, \"end\": 740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999564407268213, \"rank\": 3.245751151723692e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 656}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 678}, {\"ngram\": \"the symbol\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 707}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"its construction\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 763}, {\"ngram\": \"the symbol\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 793}, {\"ngram\": \"an outside organisation\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 820}, {\"ngram\": \"a permanent way\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 851}, {\"ngram\": \"whatever\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"its prestige\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 888}, {\"ngram\": \"the Association\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 909}, {\"ngram\": \"Gustave Eiffel's Descendants\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The association's chairman, Olivier Berthelot-Eiffel, a great-great-grandson of the engineer, told the AFP news agency that the family did not see any problem with the rings staying longer than the Paralympic Games, which wrap up on September 8.\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 1194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"AFP news agency\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The association's chairman\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 975}, {\"ngram\": \"Olivier Berthelot-Eiffel\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1001}, {\"ngram\": \"a great-great-grandson\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1025}, {\"ngram\": \"the engineer\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1041}, {\"ngram\": \"the family\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1083}, {\"ngram\": \"any problem\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympic Games\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1163}, {\"ngram\": \"September\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1191}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But the Eiffel Tower should not become an advertising outpost.\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1259, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1217}, {\"ngram\": \"an advertising outpost\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1258}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anne Hidalgo should have said that she wanted to keep the Olympic rings, not that she had decided it, and then discussed the idea with the Paris council and relevant individuals,\\\" he explained.\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1260, \"end\": 1272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 1399, \"end\": 1404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1737593392155295e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic rings\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1331}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"relevant individuals\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1437}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hidalgo told the Ouest-France newspaper on Saturday that she wanted to keep the rings and \\\"the decision is up to me, and I have the agreement of the IOC [International Olympic Committee].\\\"\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1609, \"end\": 1640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hidalgo\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1462}, {\"ngram\": \"the Ouest-France newspaper\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1494}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1540}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1558}, {\"ngram\": \"the agreement\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1596}, {\"ngram\": \"the IOC\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So, yes, they [the rings] will stay on the Eiffel Tower,\\\" she said without specifying for how long.\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1745, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rings\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1670}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1701}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hidalgo also repeated her wish to see the Olympic cauldron stay in the Tuileries Gardens, but President Emmanuel Macron will have the final say because the site is state property.\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1818, \"end\": 1835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuileries_Garden\", \"score\": 0.6045543459566789, \"rank\": 0.6541110103468648, \"text\": \"Tuileries Gardens\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuileries_Garden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuileries_Garden\"}, {\"begin\": 1851, \"end\": 1866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hidalgo\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1754}, {\"ngram\": \"her wish\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1777}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic cauldron\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1805}, {\"ngram\": \"the final say\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1907}, {\"ngram\": \"state property\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Culture Minister Rachida Dati, a longtime critic and opponent of Hidalgo, also cast doubt over the idea, saying the Socialist city leader would need to follow procedures protecting historic buildings.\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1945, \"end\": 1957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachida Dati\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachida_Dati\"}, {\"begin\": 1993, \"end\": 2000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.99999997450027, \"rank\": 2.5499777391437253e-08, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a longtime critic\", \"from\": 1959, \"to\": 1976}, {\"ngram\": \"opponent\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"doubt\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2017}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2031}, {\"ngram\": \"the Socialist city leader\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2065}, {\"ngram\": \"procedures\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2097}, {\"ngram\": \"historic buildings\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2127}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Eiffel Tower is a protected monument, the work of an immense engineer and designer,\\\" Dati said in a statement.\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2245, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2147}, {\"ngram\": \"a protected monument\", \"from\": 2151, \"to\": 2171}, {\"ngram\": \"the work\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2181}, {\"ngram\": \"an immense engineer\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"designer\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2217}, {\"ngram\": \"Dati\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2224}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2244}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Protections for its architectural merit and his work require authorisations and an impact study before any major modifications can be carried out, in line with the law on protected buildings,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Protections\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2259}, {\"ngram\": \"its architectural merit\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2287}, {\"ngram\": \"his work\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2300}, {\"ngram\": \"authorisations\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2323}, {\"ngram\": \"an impact study\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2343}, {\"ngram\": \"any major modifications\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"the law\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2415}, {\"ngram\": \"protected buildings\", \"from\": 2419, \"to\": 2438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reaction on social media was mixed, but many Parisians appeared highly dubious about modifying the symbol of the city that is also a protected UNESCO World Heritage Site.\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2603, \"end\": 2622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Heritage_Site\", \"score\": 0.9999999561389369, \"rank\": 4.386109825821281e-08, \"text\": \"World Heritage Site\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Heritage_Site\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Heritage_Site\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Reaction\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2461}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 2465, \"to\": 2477}, {\"ngram\": \"many Parisians\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2507}, {\"ngram\": \"the symbol\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2558}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2570}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Eiffel Tower has a history of 135 years and surpasses a sports and media event of 17 days,\\\" commented the SOS Paris group, which campaigns to protect Paris's landmarks and historic character.\", \"from\": 2625, \"to\": 2821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2736, \"end\": 2739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SOS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9353100944057628e-15, \"text\": \"SOS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SOS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SOS\"}, {\"begin\": 2740, \"end\": 2745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1737593392155295e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2780, \"end\": 2785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1737593392155295e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2642}, {\"ngram\": \"a history\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2656}, {\"ngram\": \"135 years\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2669}, {\"ngram\": \"a sports and media event\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"17 days\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2719}, {\"ngram\": \"historic character\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2820}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For me, this is a mistake,\\\" Paris MP Sylvain Maillard from Macron's centrist Renaissance party told France Bleu Paris radio.\", \"from\": 2823, \"to\": 2948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2852, \"end\": 2857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1737593392155295e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2883, \"end\": 2889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.734728477992726e-20, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 2901, \"end\": 2912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Renaissance\", \"score\": 0.9130101265083855, \"rank\": 0.09236430724496592, \"text\": \"Renaissance\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Renaissance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Renaissance\"}, {\"begin\": 2924, \"end\": 2935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"France Bleu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\"}, {\"begin\": 2924, \"end\": 2935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"France Bleu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Bleu\"}, {\"begin\": 2936, \"end\": 2941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1737593392155295e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a mistake\", \"from\": 2840, \"to\": 2849}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The games were a very powerful moment, but the Eiffel Tower embodies something timeless.\\\"\", \"from\": 2949, \"to\": 3039, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The games\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 2959}, {\"ngram\": \"a very powerful moment\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 2987}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3009}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Eiffel Tower was unveiled in 1889 for the World's Fair.\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3100, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3057}, {\"ngram\": \"the World's Fair\", \"from\": 3083, \"to\": 3099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reviled by some Parisians at the time, the 324-metre (1,063ft) tower of latticed steel girders was originally built as a temporary attraction to showcase French construction prowess but became a working telecommunications tower, used for radio and TV transmissions.\", \"from\": 3102, \"to\": 3367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3256, \"end\": 3262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8512956349131848, \"rank\": 0.14286485839078722, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some Parisians\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3127}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3139}, {\"ngram\": \"the 324-metre (1,063ft) tower\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3170}, {\"ngram\": \"latticed steel girders\", \"from\": 3174, \"to\": 3196}, {\"ngram\": \"a temporary attraction\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3243}, {\"ngram\": \"a working telecommunications tower\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3329}, {\"ngram\": \"radio and TV transmissions\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3366}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"Iron Lady\\\" has since become the capital's symbol and is one of the world's top tourist attractions with 6.3 million visitors in 2023.\", \"from\": 3369, \"to\": 3507, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The \\\"Iron Lady\", \"from\": 3369, \"to\": 3383}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital's symbol\", \"from\": 3402, \"to\": 3422}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's top tourist attractions\", \"from\": 3437, \"to\": 3472}, {\"ngram\": \"6.3 million visitors\", \"from\": 3478, \"to\": 3498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Al Jazeera English:\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3553, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow Al Jazeera English\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3552}]}]}"